text: Dolores County is the seventh-least populous of the 64 counties of the U.S. state of Colorado. As of the 2020 census, the population was 2,326. The county seat is Dove Creek. Dolores County was founded on February 19, 1881, and was named for the Dolores River. == References == Category:1880s establishments in Colorado Category:1881 establishments in the United States Category:Colorado counties
title: Dolores County, Colorado
